{"id": 49, "date": "2024-06-03T15:18:37", "date_gmt": "2024-06-03T20:18:37", "guid": {"rendered": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/?page_id=49"}, "modified": "2025-12-18T14:34:53", "modified_gmt": "2025-12-18T20:34:53", "slug": "hazing-transparency-report", "status": "publish", "type": "page", "link": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/hazing-transparency-report/", "title": {"rendered": "Hazing Transparency Report"}, "content": {"rendered": "\n<p>In accordance with the Stop Campus Hazing Act (SCHA), The University of Louisiana will maintain a Campus Hazing Transparency Report (CHTR). This report provides information on confirmed hazing violations by organizations formally recognized by the University. The CHTR will be updated biannually, as required.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Each situation is unique, and all allegations are addressed on a case-by-case basis. The University’s response to noted situations does not create binding precedents but may guide its handling of any similar situations that may arise in the future.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Navigate by year, then select the button with the name of the social organization whose violations you wish to view.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper  \"><ul class=\"ua_link-list ua_layout--grid\" >\n<li><a href=\"#2025\" class=\"ua_link-list_item\"> 2025</a></li>\n\n<li><a href=\"#2024\" class=\"ua_link-list_item\"> 2024</a></li>\n\n<li><a href=\"#2023\" class=\"ua_link-list_item\"> 2023</a></li>\n\n<li><a href=\"#2022\" class=\"ua_link-list_item\"> 2022</a></li>\n\n<li><a href=\"#2021\" class=\"ua_link-list_item\"> 2021</a></li>\n</ul></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"terminology\" class=\"wp-block-group is-style-elevated ua-util_mt--8 is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-e8fb96ec wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\" style=\"padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow)\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Terminology</h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper  \"><div class=\"ua_layout--grid\" >\n<div  >\n\n<dl>\n    <dt>Incident</dt>\n    <dd>Date of Hazing Incident or Citation</dd>\n    <dt>Reported</dt>\n    <dd>Date of Report to Institution</dd>\n    <dt>NHQ</dt>\n    <dd>Organization Inter/National Headquarters</dd>\n    <dt>Description</dt>\n    <dd>General Description of Hazing Incident</dd>\n    <dt>Rules Violations</dt>\n    <dd>University Rules Violations</dd>\n</dl>\n\n</div>\n\n<div  >\n\n<dl>\n    <dt>Individuals Responsible</dt>\n    <dd>Individuals Involved/Found Responsible</dd>\n    <dt>Findings</dt>\n    <dd>University Findings</dd>\n    <dt>Arrests</dt>\n    <dd>Arrests and arresting agency (not tracked with violations prior to 2024)</dd>\n    <dt>Sanctions</dt>\n    <dd>University Sanctions</dd>\n</dl>\n\n</div>\n</div></div></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignfull is-style-default is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\" id=\"rules\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-double);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-double)\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Rules Defined</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Please refer to the <a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/judicial-affairs/docs/Revised%20Code%20of%20Student%20Conduct%20Handbook.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Revised Code of Student Conduct handbook (PDF)</a> for the official standards by which students must conduct themselves. The handbook is published by the Office of Student Conduct; see also <a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/judicial-affairs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Student Conduct (Judicial Affairs) on gram.edu</a>. Examples of conduct expectations addressed in the Code include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Hazing</strong> &#8211; All forms of hazing are prohibited. For definitions, reporting, and related expectations on this site, see the <a href=\"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/what-is-hazing/ua-hazing-policy/\">GSU Hazing Policy</a> summary.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Threats and harm</strong> &#8211; Conduct that threatens or harms people or property.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Integrity</strong> &#8211; Dishonesty or furnishing false information to University officials.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Compliance</strong> &#8211; Failure to comply with sanctions or directives imposed under the student conduct process.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Published policies</strong> &#8211; Violation of other University policies incorporated by reference in the Code.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"2025\" class=\"wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">2025</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-query alignwide is-layout-flow wp-block-query-is-layout-flow\"><ul class=\"columns-3 alignwide wp-block-post-template is-layout-grid wp-container-core-post-template-is-layout-572542b5 wp-block-post-template-is-layout-grid\"><li class=\"wp-block-post post-740 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-8\">\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group sl-QueryLoop is-style-elevated is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\" style=\"padding-top:30px;padding-right:10px;padding-bottom:30px;padding-left:10px\"><h3 style=\"padding-top:0;padding-bottom:0;padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--2);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--2);margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;\" class=\"has-text-align-center wp-block-post-title has-medium-font-size\"><a href=\"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/posts/2025/2025/theta-chi/\" target=\"_self\" >Theta Chi</a></h3></div>\n\n</li><li class=\"wp-block-post post-749 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-8\">\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group sl-QueryL